title.description: You have a hankering for fine breakfasts.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Carnivore

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Pie Maven
title.description: You are a fine judge of pies.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Vegetarian
title.description: You prefer meals of vegetables and fruits.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME} ${SURNAME} the Wary
title.description: You have reached 5th level without being defeated in battle.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME} ${SURNAME} the Undefeated
title.description: You have reached 10th level without being defeated in battle.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME} ${SURNAME} the Indomitable
title.description: You have reached 14th level without being defeated in battle.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME} ${SURNAME} the Unscathed
title.description: You have reached 17th level without being defeated in battle.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME} ${SURNAME} the Undying
title.description: You have reached 20th level without being defeated in battle.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Barrow-downs Hunter
title.description: You have pursued and slain many of the Barghests who haunt the Barrow-downs.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Watcher of Roads
title.description: The folk of Bree-land hail your efforts to protect the roads from roving bandits.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Root-hewer
title.description: You've proven a match for the rotten hatred the trees of the Old Forest hold for the two-footed folk of Middle-earth.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Shell-breaker
title.description: Who would ever have thought that Neekerbreekers could grow that big?

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Defender of Bree-land
title.description: You have proven your mettle against the Orcs who have invaded northern Bree-land.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Fly-swatter
title.description: People may snicker, but how many of them have had to fight one of these giant bloodsuckers?

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Spider-foe
title.description: Spiders have become quite a threat of late in Bree-land, but your prowess against them is well known.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bane of the Barrows
title.description: The wights of the Barrow-downs no longer hold any terror for you. Now you just find them deeply unsettling.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bog-hunter
title.description: Whence came these slimy horrors that now plague the Lone-lands, no one knows, but now you have taken their measure.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Enemy of the Dead
title.description: The Lords of the gaunt-men have taken notice of your activities....

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Goblin-hewer
title.description: No matter how many goblins you kill, the Lone-lands just seems to become overrun with yet more of them.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Champion of the Lone-lands
title.description: Without your strength, it seems likely the Lone-lands would be overrun with Orcs by now.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Spider-bane
title.description: The Lone-lands, too, are infested by these eight-legged horrors, each stronger than the last -- yet still they fall before you!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Warg-hunter
title.description: Along with the goblins, Wargs have come to the Lone-lands. They'll not have free run as long as you stand against them!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Cleaver of Goblins
title.description: The goblins have retaken deep delvings carved in the hills of the North Downs, inhabiting them in great droves. While they have learned to fear your name, you don't seem to have made much of a dent in their numbers.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, ${NAME: Hero[m]| Heroine[f]} of the North Downs
title.description: Most of the residents of the North Downs have been driven away by the orkish incursion, but those few who remain now herald your name as their saviour against these brutish invaders.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Foe of Night
title.description: Long ago many princes and warriors of the Dúnedain fell upon the Fields of Fornost - you cannot say if these horrors are them, but either way you've returned many of them to the peace of the grave.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Troll-hewer
title.description: Trolls -- they are among the strongest and perhaps the least intelligent of the servants of the Enemy. Now it seems that these inhuman giants wander the North Downs at will, or would, if you did not stand against them!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Warg-foe
title.description: Anywhere goblins can be found, you'll likely encounter Wargs. Thanks to your valiant efforts there are fewer of them in the North Downs however.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Worm-slayer
title.description: Legend has it that the Enemy spent long ages devising the great breed of Dragons that have bedeviled Middle-earth. Worms are among the lesser forms that were discarded along the way - but they are still deadly foes, and more common than their greater kin.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bounders-friend
title.description: The bounders of the Shire look on you kindly for your help in dealing with the recent brigand troubles.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Protector of the Shire
title.description: It has been long since the brood of Golfimbul endangered the folk of the Shire, but they will have to make it past you first.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Crop-saviour
title.description: The harvest-flies are more of a threat to the crops than to the folk of the Shire, but the farmers are thankful for your efforts to exterminate them.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Slug-squasher
title.description: You're not sure that this was the title you were looking for when you set out on the path of an adventurer....

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Spider-sting
title.description: Like so many places in Middle-earth, the Shire has seen a recent infestation of dangerous spiders, but they have learned to fear your sting!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Fur-cutter
title.description: Just as in olden days, wolves again threaten the Shire, but you have taught them a lesson they'll not soon forget.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Defender of the Halls
title.description: The Dourhands have proven a sore thorn in the side of Durin's Folk, having lost the respect and trust of their kin.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Guardian of Ered Luin
title.description: Ancestral foes of dwarf and Elf alike, goblins again challenge the lands of Ered Luin, but you stand ready to defy them.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Feather-foe
title.description: Unlike the noble Eagles, the crooked hendrovail are used as spies for dark masters across many lands -- Ered Luin included.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Web-slasher
title.description: Spiders have long lurked in all the dark corners of Middle-earth, but those of Ered Luin, at least, have reason to fear you.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Wolf-tamer
title.description: Driven down from the frozen north, wolves are a constant challenge to all those who live in Ered Luin, but your prowess has proven their master.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Doom of the Angmarim
title.description: These evil Men wield terrible powers granted them by their Dark Lord -- but such magic will avail them not as you pursue them into the deepest corners of their great strongholds in the north.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bane of the Orcs
title.description: Numbering in the tens of thousands, Orcs have long formed the mainstay of the Enemy's armies. You long ago lost count of how many of these foul creatures have fallen before you - and yet their numbers seem undiminished.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bane of Trolls
title.description: The trolls of Angmar are the deadliest of all you have faced. Wielding arms and armour from the forges of the Enemy and possesed of a cruel cunning, even great heroes have fallen before their might.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Warlord of Angmar
title.description: The mighty Uruk form the elite forces of the armies of Angmar. Having defeated so many of their kind in battle, your name now commands a certain respect - and even deeper enmity - among their ranks.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, ${NAME: Lord[m]| Lady[f]} of Fangs
title.description: The dreadful Wargs raised within the kennels of Angmar have known no other masters - until now. Still, it seems they are not about to let you pet them.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Destiny of the Accursed
title.description: Angmar hosts a dread valley of spirits enthralled to the power of the Witch-King, and they do his bidding in his absence. There are few places in all Middle-Earth that inspire such dread as those halls - the Orcs and goblins give it wide breadth, while only the most fanatical of the Angmarim will enter to perform dark rites therein.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Weird of the Worms
title.description: Mishaphen half-children of the great Dragons of old, the Worms of Angmar possess a fair portion of their elder brood's power and cunning. Yet you have overcome their power and proven their match.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bear-wrestler
title.description: You've heard that the giants sometimes breed the largest bears as pets - and that wouldn't surprise you. They grow them big here in the Misty Mountains - really big.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bane of Titans
title.description: You'd thought these great creatures must be legend and myth when you were told stories of them by your parents. Not any more. Their strength is as great as their size, and their bravery that of a creature that knows it is unmatched. Nevertheless, the valour of you and your companions has laid many of these titans low in battle.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Beast-hunter
title.description:
The Snow-beasts that inhabit the Misty Mountains are odd creatures. You'd only heard vague tales of them before you came there, and most people would consider them myths, but you've fought enough of them to be quite sure they are real.
Where they may have come from is anyone's guess. Perhaps the Enemy found them far in the distant North somewhere, beyond the boundaries of Man or Elf.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Vanquisher of Trolls
title.description: As if the biting cold in the Misty Mountains wasn't bad enough, it seems to have given rise to a particularly unpleasant breed of troll. These creatures thrive in the ice and frost, and they lurk here waiting to crush and devour any traveller unlucky enough to stumble upon them.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Warg-hunter
title.description: Where there are goblins there are Wargs, and the Misty Mountains are no exception. Tempered by the deadly cold and harsh conditions, these Wargs have become particularly vicious and deadly but you've found them to be passable opponents at best.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Worm-bane
title.description: It is said that worms have long lived in the far north, among the desolate and frozen wastes. Alas, it seems only natural then that as the gates of Angmar have been laid open that they should have unleashed many of the creatures into the frozen peaks of the Misty Mountains, there to breed and to terrorize any who attempt the dangerous passage.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Chitin-smasher
title.description: And here you'd thought nothing could be worse than the bugs in Midgewater. These many legged horrors have changed your mind on the matter, but not stopped your battle to protect Middle-earth.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Giant-slayer
title.description: It took more than a flyswatter to bring down so many of these prodigious foes - a feat for which you are rightly renowned.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Troll-slayer
title.description: These lands weren't named the Trollshaws without good reason. You've certainly found no shortage of the brutes to test your mettle against!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, the Purifier
title.description: Even the Elves of Rivendell claim not to know whence the horrid wights infesting the Trollshaws came. Nevertheless you have forced many of them back into the earth from which they escaped.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Tail-cleaver
title.description: The wolves that inhabit the Trollshaws are among the most wild and powerful of that breed. Serving neither Man nor Goblin, these wolves prey upon any foolish enough to venture into their territory - save for you.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Worm-carver
title.description: Where could so many of these terrible beasts have been hidden away? The wastes of the far North, or buried beneath the Gates of Angmar? It doesn't really matter where they came from, so long as you strive to drive them from the lands of Middle-earth.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Conqueror of the Ettenmoors
title.description: You have defeated each of the great Tyrants of the Ettenmoors and your power is renowned among all those who fight under the banner of the Free People.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Shire Brewmaster
title.description: An expert in the beers and ales of the Shire.

title.description: You are a member within a Kinship.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME} ${SURNAME} of Bree-land
title.description: You grew up in Bree-land, once part of the North Kingdom of Arnor, once ruled by Elendil the Tall as High King of Middle-earth, and later by his elder son Isildur. Now it is but a simple, rustic land, and the North Kingdom is no more.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME} ${SURNAME} of Dale
title.description: You come from the Dale-lands in the north-east of Middle-earth, beneath the Lonely Mountain, where Bard the Bowman slew the dragon Smaug and fought in the Battle of Five Armies.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME} ${SURNAME} of Gondor
title.description: You hail from the land of Gondor, the South Kingdom once ruled conjointly by the sons of Elendil, Isildur and Anárion, ever-watchful against the looming threat of Mordor.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME} ${SURNAME} of Rohan
title.description: You are one of the Horse-lords of the Riddermark, the realm granted to Eorl the Young by Cirion, Steward of Gondor, currently ruled by Théoden, son of Thengel.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME} ${SURNAME} of the Fallohides
title.description: Lovers of trees and woodlands, the Fallohides were the first hobbits to come to the Shire. They generally tend to be fairer of skin and hair, as well as taller and more slender.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME} ${SURNAME} of the Harfoots
title.description: The Harfoots are the most prodigious hole-dwellers and were the first to cross west into Eriador. They generally tend to be browner of skin than the other kindreds, as well as smaller and shorter.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME} ${SURNAME} of the Stoors
title.description: The Stoors were the last of the hobbit kindreds to come to the Shire, settling at last in the eastern marshlands of the Shire. They generally tend to be heavier and broader of build than the other kindreds.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME} ${SURNAME} of the Iron Hills
title.description: You come from the Iron Hills, settled by dwarves as a refuge from the Cold-drakes, and whence came Dáin Ironfoot, King under the Mountain, kinsman of the great Thorin Oakenshield.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME} ${SURNAME} of the Lonely Mountain
title.description: You hail from Erebor, the Lonely Mountain, where Smaug the Golden made his lair until Thorin Oakenshield reclaimed it for his people. There does Dáin Ironfoot now rule as King under the Mountain.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME} ${SURNAME} of the Blue Mountains
title.description: Your home is in Ered Luin, the Blue Mountains, where there had once been two great dwarf-kingdoms and where the kinsmen of Thráin and his son Thorin Oakenshield lived in exile after Smaug drove them from the Lonely Mountain.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME} ${SURNAME} of the Grey Mountains
title.description: You are from Ered Mithrin, the Grey Mountains, the chief of which is Mount Gundabad, from whence came Durin the Deathless, first Father of the Dwarves. Your kindred returned to the Mountains after the Dragons perished.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME} ${SURNAME} of the White Mountains
title.description: You are from the south-western halls of Ered Nimrais, the White Mountains in the south bordering the lands of Andrast. Though your kingdom lies far from the central mountains where Men once dwelt, the rumour of the Oathbreakers has given your realm an ill name.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME} ${SURNAME} of Lindon
title.description: You hail from Lindon, the green lands of the Elves between Ered Luin and the Sea, where Gil-galad, the last great Elf-king, once ruled. Círdan the Shipwright now rules there from Mithlond, the Grey Havens.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME} ${SURNAME} of Lórien
title.description: You come from Lothlórien, the fabled golden woods whose Elves dwell high in the mallorn-trees and are ruled by Celeborn, wisest of the Eldar of Middle-earth, and the Lady Galadriel.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME} ${SURNAME} of Mirkwood
title.description: You are a Wood-elf of Mirkwood, once called Greenwood the Great, where King Thranduil keeps watch against the growing darkness of Dol Guldur, former stronghold of Sauron in his guise as the Necromancer.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME} ${SURNAME} of Rivendell
title.description: You hail from Imladris, called Rivendell by Men, built by Elrond Halfelven as a refuge for the Elves of Eregion as they fled destruction at the hands of Sauron.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME} ${SURNAME} of Edhellond
title.description: You are of the Nandor of Edhellond, the great Elf-haven in the south built by Amroth at the Mouths of Anduin.

title.description: Mordirith, leader of Angmar in the stead of the Witch-king, looks upon you as a trusted servant. His favour will earn you greater favour with the Lugburz!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Conqueror of Ringdyr
title.description: You have defeated the captains of Ringdyr.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Conqueror of Tol Ascarnen
title.description: You have defeated the captains of Tol Ascarnen.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Conqueror of the Towers
title.description: You have defeated the captains of the Towers.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Snitch-killer
title.description: You've hunted down a number of these annoying little backstabbers and shown them what it means to oppose the will of Angmar.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Thief-slayer
title.description: Those who would steal from the lords of Angmar will die by the sword, and at your hands many of them have.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Burglar-basher
title.description: Never trust a thief. For that matter, don't trust anyone.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bane of Shadows
title.description: Burglars can run, but they cannot hide from you. You've killed a great many of these filthy little sneaks in your time.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Trickster's Scourge
title.description: Tricksy and false? Hah! You've seen how 'tricksy' Burglars are when they are writhing in pain as you prepare to strike the killing blow. It's hardly even a sporting challenge any more.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Captain's Foe
title.description: These fools would lead the forces of Men? Then let them lead from the grave!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Captain-slayer
title.description: Rally their allies to them as they might, you've cut through and killed many of these banner-waving cretins.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Banner-shredder
title.description: The banners make them easy to spot on the battlefield, and ripe for the killing as you and your hordes fall upon them from the darkness.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bane of Order
title.description: Without their leaders, the forces of Men often fall to panic and cowardly flight. You have excelled at extinguishing these little sparks of false 'hope' upon the field of battle.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Defiler of Lords
title.description:
Few things warm your dark heart quite like the crestfallen look upon the faces of your enemies as yet another of their Lords falls in battle before you.
It is a sight you have enjoyed so very often...

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Champion's Foe
title.description: These self-righteous crusaders have often fallen before your own unheralded strength.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Slayer of Champions
title.description: Champions respect strength above all else - a trait which you have displayed in plenty as you've hewed through their ranks.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Sword-breaker
title.description:
He who lives by the sword had best expect to die by it.
You make a point of giving these fool Champions every opportunity to do so at your hands.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bane of Courage
title.description:
What good is courage to one who lies, broken and bleeding beneath your feet? Who knows?
Who cares.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Doom of Heroes
title.description: Hah! For self-styled 'Heroes', these Champions fall like wheat before the scythe of your power. They are no match for you, nor shall they ever be!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Guardian-killer
title.description:
These self-styled Guardians stand between you and the towns and villages of the West, which lie ripe for the plucking.
The more of them you kill, the sooner you can start the looting.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Sentinel-slayer
title.description: Why would these iron-hided scum stand between you and the weak? You'll never understand it - but you've proven they can be swept aside all the same.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Shield-breaker
title.description: Though they carry great shields and clothe themselves in burnished steel, no-one may stand before the power of Angmar and live. You've seen to that.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Guardian's Bane
title.description:
Defenders of the Weak indeed! Who then shall defend these supposed Guardians from you, eh?
No-one, that's who...

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Doom of the Stalwart
title.description:
Those who stand before the tide are doomed to drown in its fury.
You charge in the vanguard of the endless armies of Angmar and crush those Guardians who dare to stand with armies of the West, without mercy or hesitation.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Hunter-killer
title.description: These vicious opponents would attempt to sap the strength of Angmar from afar, you've found it best to take the battle to them in person.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Scout-blinder
title.description: You've killed your share of the enemy's scouts. They would do better to cower behind their allies in battle, but then what's the sport in that?

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bow-cleaver
title.description: With neither shield or armour, Hunters make for easy prey upon the battlefield. Sure the arrows sting a bit, but pain is the mark of a true warrior.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Hunter's Bane
title.description: Ah, the joy when the tables are turned and the Hunter becomes the Hunted! So many of these miscreants have fallen before you now that you've nearly lost count.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Doom of the Archer
title.description: Bows may be fearsome weapons in skilled hands, but they cannot protect their wielders from the swift and certain death that you bring upon them in battle. They are just more kindling for the bonfires of Angmar!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Lore-master's Foe
title.description: The Wise? feh! The truly Wise need understand only power. Those who profess wisdom in knowledge often die at your hands.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Sage-slayer
title.description: No magic can protect these bookworms from your wrath. If they understood even a fraction of the power commanded by the Lords of Angmar, they would cower in abject surrender before death.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Staff-breaker
title.description: What's so special about a staff? Just another stick to be broken - right before you break the one who wields it, as you have so often before.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bane of the Wise
title.description: What good are old books and a fine pointy hat when you've got three feet of steel protruding from your gut? None at all! You've proved the wisdom of that statement often enough.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Scourge of the Learned
title.description:
No overblown scribe can challenge you on the battlefield.
Scrolls, books, staves, robes - all shall burn in the bonfires of Angmar!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Minstrel's Foe
title.description:
What kind of fool comes to the battlefield to sing rather than fight?
A dead fool.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bard-slayer
title.description: The songs of the West sound far more pleasing to your ears when they gurgle forth from a slit throat.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Harp-cutter
title.description: The discordant snapping of strings, the splintering of wood, and the screams of the dying are all the music needed to accompany your rampage.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Troubador's Bane
title.description:
The leaderless scum of the West are said to believe that the world was born from a song.
Perhaps, perhaps not, but the last music they shall hear before their fall shall be the war-drums of Angmar!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Silencer of Songs
title.description:
In the wake of your passage, the fields of battle take on an unnatural stillness broken only by the moans of the dying.
No songs escape from the lips of the fallen, for no life remains to utter them.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Pie-eating Champion
title.description: You won a pie-eating contest.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Gundzor's Drudge
title.description: You have assisted Gundzor earning the rank of drudge.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Gundzor's Flunky
title.description: You have continued to assist Gundzor earning the rank of flunky.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Gundzor's Fist
title.description: You have become known to Gundzor as more than a servant; you are a defender of his post in the Grimwood.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bûrzgoth's Thrall
title.description: You have assisted Bûrzgoth and earned the title of his thrall.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bûrzgoth's Toady
title.description: You have continued to assist Bûrzgoth and earned the right to be his toady.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bûrzgoth's Bootlicker
title.description: You have become known to Bûrzgoth as one who will do as he says, when he says.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Tharbil's Minion
title.description: You have assisted the master of Lugazag and earned the right to be at his beck and call.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Tharbil's Lackey
title.description: You have continued to assist the master of Lugazag and firmed your position as his servant.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Tharbil's Whip
title.description: You have become known to Tharbil as more than a servant; you are a defender of his post at Lugazag.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Servant to Barashish
title.description: You have assisted the master of Tirith Rhaw and earned station as his servant.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Hound to Barashish
title.description: You have earned greater favour of the master of Tirith Rhaw and can now be named a hound. A loyal dog.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Blade of Barashish
title.description: You have become known to Barashish as more than a servant; you are a defender of his post at Tirith Rhaw.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Trintrû Truckler
title.description: You have assisted the master of Tol Ascarnen and earned the right to be called a truckler.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Trintrû's Lickspittle
title.description: You have continued to assist Trintrû earning the right to be called his lickspittle.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Trintrû's Sycophant
title.description: None question your devotion to Trintrû, thus you are called his sycophant.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Pie-runner
title.description: Helping Holly Hornblower has honoured her and hastened hungry hobbits into happy hobbits.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} of the Quick Post
title.description: For your help to the Quick Post, Postmaster Proudfoot has declared you an official postman.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Hand of Doom
title.description: With your coming sounds the trump of Doom, for by your hand have many of the warriors of the Free Peoples fallen bested by your might.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Elf-slayer
title.description: Your legend has grown so much amongst the Elves that you are now a true villain. They know only to run from you when you near them!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Enemy of Valour
title.description: Valour crumbles when you near. The dwarves' courage spills from them as easily as their innards when you are about. The death delivered by your hands sunders hope.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Man-foe
title.description: Men quake at the mention of your name, as your blade bites deeply into their flesh.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Hobbit-bane
title.description: Your continued destruction of the little folk drives a spike of fear into their hearts.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Slayer of Light
title.description: Light ebbs in your presence. Strength leaves the enemy as the darkness you bring clouds their hope and drives dread into their hearts.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Elf-bane
title.description: Your name is known amongst the Elves. It is used to strike fear into the hearts of the young.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Scourge of the Undermountain
title.description: When Angmar's Army moves beneath the world to face the dwarves in their mountain homes, perhaps you shall be the one to lead it. You have proven yourself most adept at slaying these vermin!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, War-boss
title.description: You are an officer within a Tribe.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Hobbit-slayer
title.description: Without compassion or care you flay flesh from the little folk and have become one of the most adept at culling their number from the world.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bone-speaker
title.description: You are the founder of a Tribe.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Herald of Darkness
title.description: You are a herald of the Dark Lord. You have culled countless numbers from the field of battle and none escape your grasp.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Dwarf-tosser
title.description: Dwarves quake before you! You cleave and heave their bodies aside by the hundred!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Chieftain
title.description: You are a leader within a Tribe.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Warlord
title.description: You are the founder of a Tribe.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bane of the West
title.description: You are known as the Bane of the West, for none of their warriors can stand against you, and windrows of their fallen lie heaped in your wake.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Dwarf-bane
title.description: Continued efforts against the dwarves earn you great glory. You are seen as their bane by others in Angmar's ranks.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Field-master
title.description: You are an officer within a Tribe.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Hobbit-foe
title.description: Slaughtering the little folk has earned you a mark of savagery against their kind.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Sentinel
title.description: You are an officer within a Tribe.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Dwarf-foe
title.description: Your victories against the bearded folk beneath the mountain brand you their foe.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Enemy of Honour
title.description: Countless deaths by your hand tarnish Men. Their honour breaks as easily as their wills when you stride onto the fields of battle.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Scourge of Man
title.description: Men fear you. There are none who do not know your name in battle and all Men quake in terror at its mention.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Elf-foe
title.description: Your blade has tasted the flesh of many Elves and it desires the blood of more.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Warrior
title.description: You are a leader within a Tribe.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Man-flayer
title.description: Cleaving through the ranks of Men drives you to near frenzy. You are known for slaughter and tearing flesh from Men.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Grunt
title.description: You are a grunt within a Tribe.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Grunt
title.description: You are a grunt within a Tribe.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Tormenter
title.description: You are known as a tormenter of the Free Peoples.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Man-slayer
title.description: Your blade drinks the blood of Man freely. There are few who would stand against you!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}
title.description: Your rank, name, and surname, sans title.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Battle-master
title.description: You are a leader within a Tribe.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Ancestor
title.description: You are the founder of a Tribe.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Warmonger
title.description: You are a leader within a Tribe.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Grunt
title.description: You are a grunt within a Tribe.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Watcher
title.description: You are an officer within a Tribe.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Harvester of Sorrow
title.description: The field of battle serves as a garden from which you reap the heads of the fallen. You are a true harvester of sorrow.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Enemy of Grace
title.description: Grace falters when you draw close. There are none amongst the Elves who will stand before you. The destruction wrought by your hand has crippled grace.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Scourge of the Little Folk
title.description: There are no little folk who dare stand before you. Your prowess over them is known to all as you tear through them with impunity.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Overseer
title.description: You are the founder of a Tribe.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Grunt
title.description: You are a grunt within a Tribe.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Black Dog
title.description: Angmar casts a favouring eye upon you, you are known as an elite amongst their number. A hound of Mordirith; a Black Dog!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Scourge of the Fair Folk
title.description: All who draw breath and hold ties to the Elven Folk fear your blade. You drive their number from the fields of battle.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Enemy of Innocence
title.description: Your domination over the little folk is absolute. The blood spilled by your hands has soiled the innocence these creatures once enjoyed.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Warden of Eriador
title.description: Warden title for administrators.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Marshal of Eriador
title.description: Marshal title for administrators.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Steward of Eriador
title.description: Steward title for administrators.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Servant of Angmar
title.description: You are now indoctrinated to Angmar's Army!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, a Light from the Shadow
title.description: You have completed part one of the first volume of the Shadows of Angmar.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Tomb-warden
title.description: You have slain a great many of the tomb-robbers that threaten the burial places of the Kings of Annúminas.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Keeper of Mysteries
title.description: Some secret lies hidden within the glimmering lights that haunt the fields of Evendim -- it seems on the tip of your tongue, but ever eludes you….

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Slayer of the Gauredain
title.description: The savage Gauredain have learned to respect your strength, and perhaps even fear you -- if they ever allowed themselves to show fear in battle.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Enemy of the Giants
title.description: The Stone-giants inhabiting the hills above Evendim have come to call you their foe, and they plan for the day when they might have their vengeance upon you.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Goblin-foe
title.description: The goblins and the strange little boggarts that creep about the fringes of Evendim have learned to give you wide berth if they value their lives at all.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bane of the Kergrim
title.description:
Thus far you have laid waste to the deadly Kergrim and have not yet fallen prey to their vicious claws.
Should the day come when you make a mistake in battle against them, not even your bones will be left for others to mourn.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Quencher of Flames
title.description: The salamanders of Evendim have tried time and again to destroy you, to no avail as their fire flickers and dims before your might.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Inn League Member
title.description: For completing the Inn League's grueling test, you are now a true member.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Flying Feathers Champion
title.description: For winning a Hobnanigans match as a member of the Flying Feathers team.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Chicken Chaser
title.description: For winning a Hobnanigans match as a member of the Steel Beaks team.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Doom of Thorog Reborn
title.description: Even the reborn dragon Thorog has fallen before you.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Reclaimer of Mírdanant
title.description: Many worked together to bring this victory, but you stand above the rest, a true hero.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Slayer of the Servants Three
title.description: The Servants Three are no more, but you prevail.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Enemy of the Corcur
title.description: The Corcur of Helegrod know your name, but speak it in frightened whispers.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Enemy of Angmar
title.description: Angmar now fears your name and the names of your allies.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Venomous
title.description: You have harvested the evil venom of Zaudru's brood to serve the greater good.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Hated by Zaudru
title.description: Many of the brood of Zaudru have fallen to your might.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Dispatcher of Zaudru
title.description: Not even the foul Zaudru can stand before you.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Storvâgûn's End
title.description: Storvâgûn's treachery, and his life, have been ended.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Giant Dues-collector
title.description: Those who sold their loyalty for riches have tasted the vengeance of the righteous.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Hatchery Raider
title.description: Less ice-hatchlings now and less drakes later, a victory for the Free Peoples!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, the Selfless
title.description: Being a true hero requires more than strength of arms and will.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Executioner of the Wicked
title.description: Amongst the rotting horror of Haudh Iarchith, a gathering of corrupt and evil entities holds sway over a dark court - or at least, they did, before you found and destroyed them.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Nemesis of the Fallen
title.description: Many fallen spirits roam the dark tunnels of Haudh Iarchith, yet if there is anything that they might fear amongst the living, it is you.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Brood-hunter
title.description: The evil spider Gwigon has made its lair amongst the twisting barrow of Haudh Iarchith and there his brood multiplies, save for your efforts to exterminate them.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Grave-digger
title.description: So many corpses have clawed up from their graves amongst the labyrinthine barrows of Haudh Iarchith, that it seems you have more need of a shovel than a sword.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Master of Beasts
title.description:
A number of vicious and corrupt beasts reside within the ruins of Sarnúr, and they have fallen under the sway of the Dourhands and their allies.
Your will and strength has mastered these vermin nevertheless.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Betrayer's Bane
title.description: The Dourhand brigands have established a stronghold within the ancient ruins of Sarnúr, but your battles against them have thinned their numbers and weakened their hold on it.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Avenger of Sarnúr
title.description: An alliance of enemies plots against Ered Luin from within the ancient ruins of Sarnúr, as the traitorous Dourhand seek to bring an array of forces to bear against their hated cousins the Longbeards - luckily, your excursions into the ruins have resulted in the deaths of many of their leaders.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Troll-kicker
title.description:
It seems that the trolls inhabiting Sarnúr are of a particularly dim-witted - if brutal - strain.
Under the guidance of the Dourhands however, they cannot be ignored - though how long their allegiance might last is uncertain…

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, The Unwise
title.description: You ate the cheese even after observing all of the warning signs. This makes you especially unwise.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Servant of Process
title.description: Let it be known to all Men, Elves, dwarves, and hobbits (hereinafter 'the Free Peoples') that Will Tuffin, being of suitable age and discretion and found within the boundaries of the Shire, has been served with process in accordance with applicable law and with all due diligence by the bearer of this title. The complainant, Hob Hillbrow, seeks reasonably foreseeable damages as well as exemplary damages, if it please the Court. Respectfully submitted by a servant of process in the case.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Crosser of Roads
title.description: There are many deep secrets in Middle Earth, but you have great insight into what part the chickens play in it all.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Friend of the Wild
title.description: You have proven yourself to be a friend of the creatures of the wild.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Wing-cutter
title.description: These winged villains are little more than pests, but if it is true that they do indeed spy for the dark powers, then it is best that you have rid the Lone-lands of so many of them.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Troll-beater
title.description: One more victory for you and your allies - one less troll to worry about later.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Mentor of Song
title.description: You have passed on your knowledge of music and song to others who shall carry on the tradition.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Exemplar of Song
title.description: You have been a particularly diligent mentor to those who would learn of music and song, and have spread your knowledge to many students.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Vanquisher of Thaurlach
title.description: With the aid of your brave fellows and the High Elf Glathlírel, you have destroyed the dread Balrog Thaurlach!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, ${NAME: Lord[m]| Lady[f]} of the Shattered Chain
title.description: Yours was the hand to take up Thaurlach's shattered chain, and bear it forth into the light as proof of your company's great deeds.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Ruination of Thrâng
title.description: The Orc-chieftain Thrâng has fallen before the bravery and skill of you and your fellows, bringing you one step closer to destroying his dark master.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Saviour of the Eldgang
title.description: Your battles within the rift have aided the Eldgang Giants, who continue to struggle against the powers of darkness even in this terrible place.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bearer of Hope
title.description: You have completed part two of the first volume of the Shadows of Angmar.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Fathomer of Riddles
title.description: You have skilfully matched wits with a Riddle-master and solved the most puzzling of riddles!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Fashionable
title.description: You are strongly aware that you only get one chance to make a first impression, and take great care to ensure that your garments are up to the task!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Unfashionable
title.description: You do care about appearances, but your look would benefit from a little more time spent on simple coordination.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Eye-sore
title.description: Your choices strongly suggest that you set out to insult the entire Tailoring profession and all those who hold it dear. If you're trying to make a statement, you certainly have!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Sage of Rhudaur
title.description: You have done great work in aiding Nethraw in his study of Rhudarian History.

title.description: For helping the Inn League members with their tasks, you have been promoted to Notable status. With great pride will you wear this title among the people.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Inn League Senior Member
title.description: For helping the Inn League members with their tasks, you have been promoted to Senior Member status.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Inn League Sage of Fine Spirits
title.description: After consuming spirits from around Eriador, you are now a sage of the Inn League.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Triumphant
title.description: Against all odds, you have proven triumphant in a great test of skill and wit!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Worldly Traveller
title.description: There are few paths in Middle-earth that you have not trod.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Greeter of Kin
title.description: You are always quick with a smile and a warm hello!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Loyal
title.description: Your loyalty is second to none.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Pillar of the Community
title.description: Your selfless actions for others have not gone unnoticed!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, ANNIVERSARY TITLE
title.description: You've performed the number of quests required to complete the Lord of the Rings Anniversary Event!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, ${NAME: Hero[m]| Heroine[f]} of the Lost
title.description: The help you provided to the members of the Lost Fellowship will not soon be forgotten.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Brute of Angmar
title.description: You have served satisfactorily in the recent battles against the so-called 'Free Peoples' of Eriador!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Savage of Angmar
title.description: You have served well in the recent battles against the so-called 'Free Peoples' of Eriador!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Fiend of Angmar
title.description: You have pleased your masters during the recent battles against the so-called 'Free Peoples' of Eriador!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Horror of Angmar
title.description: You have excelled in your efforts in the recent battles against the so-called 'Free Peoples' of Eriador!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Battle-master of Angmar
title.description: You have struck terror into the hearts of the Free Peoples of Eriador!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, High Battle-master of Angmar
title.description: You have strived as no other to destroy the hopes of the Free Peoples of Eriador!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Friend of the Free Peoples
title.description: You have served ably in the offensive against the dread powers of Angmar!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Ally of the Free Peoples
title.description: You have served well in the offensive against the dread powers of Angmar!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Protector of the Free Peoples
title.description: You have served with skill in the offensive against the dread powers of Angmar!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Vindicator of the Free Peoples
title.description: You have served most impressively in the offensive against the dread powers of Angmar!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, ${NAME: Hero[m]| Heroine[f]} of the Free Peoples
title.description: You have served with great bravery in the offensive against the dread powers of Angmar!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, High ${NAME: Lord[m]| Lady[f]} of the Free People
title.description: You have served as an example of heroism in the offensive against the dread powers of Angmar!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Angmar's Bane
title.description: Your efforts to thwart the plans of the Angmarim in Forochel have earned you their eternal enmity.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Warden of the Mines
title.description: At every turn, you ensure that the Dourhands can make no false claim upon the works of their honourable brethren.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Repulser of Savages
title.description: You have stood stalwart against the savage assaults of the Gauradain and remain unbowed!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME} ${SURNAME} the Ice-render
title.description: You have felt the slashing cold of the Grim spirits of ice that you have fought for so long that it has lost its piercing sting.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Fang-breaker
title.description: The great feral cats of Forochel shall not prey upon you or your allies so long as you live.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Wrath of Winter
title.description: Even among the Wise, the great variety of dragon-kind unleashed by the ancient Enemy is not well accounted, but these creatures of the ice have met their match in you nonetheless.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, the Complete Angler
title.description: Through skill and persistence, you have successfully landed a 50lb Salmon!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Apprentice Angler
title.description: You are an Apprentice Angler.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Journeyman Angler
title.description: You are a Journeyman Angler.

title.description: You are a Master Angler.

title.description: You are an Expert Angler.

title.description: You have helped recover some of the lost Ring-lore of Eregion for Lord Elrond of Rivendell.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Revealer of the Lost
title.description: You have helped recover numerous fragments and scraps of the lost Ring-lore of Eregion for Lord Elrond of Rivendell.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Seeker of Truth
title.description: You have helped recover a great deal of the lost Ring-lore of Eregion for Lord Elrond of Rivendell.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Master of Forgotten Lore
title.description: Few have as many fragments and scraps of the Lost Ring-lore of Eregion for Lord Elrond as you.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Defender of the Ashen Wastes
title.description: You have confronted many foes within Urugarth and ably defeated them all - even the fearsome Lhugrien has fallen to your skill.

title.description: You have confronted many foes within Urugarth and ably defeated them all - even the mighty Gruglok has falled to your skill.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Champion of the Ashen Wastes
title.description: You have confronted many foes within Urugarth and ably defeated them all - even the vicious Lagmas has fallen to your skill.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Mighty
title.description: You have fearlessly strode into Urugarth and slain many Orcs in the defence of Eriador.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Strong
title.description: You have fearlessly strode into Urugarth and slain many trolls in the defence of Eriador.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Agile
title.description: You have fearlessly strode into Urugarth and slain many beasts in the defence of Eriador.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Eyes Against The Enemy
title.description: Through your efforts, the plans of the Enemy have been discovered.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Torch-bearer
title.description: The Foul Idols of Urugarth have been destroyed by your hand.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Warden of the Ashen Wastes
title.description: You have confronted many foes within Carn Dûm and ably defeated them all - even the foul Helchgam has fallen to your skill.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, ${NAME: Lord[m]| Lady[f]} of the Ashen Wastes
title.description: You have confronted many foes within Carn Dûm and ably defeated them all - even Mordirith, the Steward of Angmar, has fallen to your skill.

title.description: You have confronted many foes within Carn Dûm and ably defeated them all - even the powerful Tárlakh has fallen to your skill.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Fearless
title.description: You have fearlessly strode into Carn Dûm and slain the Ancient Evil within in the defence of Eriador.

title.description: You have fearlessly strode into Carn Dûm and slain many slugs in the defence of Eriador.

title.description: You have fearlessly strode into Carn Dûm and slain many Angmarim in the defence of Eriador.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Foil of War
title.description: Through your efforts, the plans of the Enemy have been discovered.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Keeper of Books
title.description: The ancient lore of the Enemy has come into your hands! With this information, the Council of the North can better defend against the forces of Angmarim and the terror within Barad Gúlaran.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Defender Against the Terror
title.description: You have confronted many foes within Barad Gúlaran and ably defeated them all - even the terrible Udúnion has fallen to your skill.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Steadfast
title.description: You have fearlessly strode into Barad Gúlaran and slain many Angmarim in the defence of Eriador.

title.description: You have fearlessly strode into Barad Gúlaran and slain many Hill-men in the defence of Eriador.
