title.description: You have fearlessly strode into Annúminas and slain many Angmarim in the defence of Eriador.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Defender of Annúminas
title.description: You have confronted many foes within Annúminas and ably defeated them all - even the mighty Guldurchir has fallen to your skill.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Protector of Annúminas
title.description: You have confronted many foes within Annúminas and ably defeated them all - even the wretched Balhest has fallen to your skill.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Righteous
title.description: You have fearlessly strode into Annúminas and slain many of the Dead within in the defence of Eriador.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Formidable
title.description: You have fearlessly strode into Annúminas and slain many Gertheryg within in the defence of Eriador.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Warden of Annúminas
title.description: Your efforts within Annúminas have not gone unnoticed by the Rangers. Because of your unceasing aid in the defence of the City of the Kings, they have bestowed upon you the title of Warden.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Pork-chopper
title.description: For too long, the Boars have plagued the land. In your efforts, you have shown a desire to drive the vile Boar-kind from Middle-earth.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Sage of the Sunken City
title.description: You have found and protected the hidden lore of the city of Annúminas before it could be delivered to the hands of Amarthiel's captains.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Moria Expeditionary
title.description: The great halls of Moria lay waiting in darkness. Rumours abound that the gate has been thrown open, and you yearn to explore its depths.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Seeker of Khazad-dûm
title.description: Long have the gates of Khazad-dûm lay hidden from the world - but now great tremors well up to shake the very mountains, and the mysteries of the deep call out to those brave enough to seek them.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Mithril-hunter
title.description: Many whisper that the halls of Moria lay littered with scraps of precious true-silver. No foolish rumours of unnamed evils will keep you from such rich treasures!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Beak-breaker
title.description: Caveclaws will stay out of sight when you are near...that is, if they are wise.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Drake-smasher
title.description: The little drakes are no less evil than their larger kindred, and your endeavours to swat them down have not been in vain.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bane of the Infected
title.description: The Globsnaga of Moria infect the very air they breathe, but you have hindered the spread of their poison.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Goblin-bane
title.description: Goblin populations should be curbed wherever in Middle-earth they are found.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bug Crusher
title.description: Many vile skittering things have been snuffed out by your persistent squashing.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Wing-breaker
title.description: You have taken down many evil merrevail in Moria.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Vanquisher of the Nameless
title.description: The origin of the Nameless in Moria is unknown, but they are wholly evil, and you have done well to act against them.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Orc-foe
title.description: The Orcs of Moria mean to do as much harm as they can to the dwarves who try to live there, but you have made the dark a little safer in your merciless defence of Khazad-dûm.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Unyielding
title.description: The spawn of Ungoliant seek to further blacken the darkness of Moria, but you have curbed their evil intentions.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Troll-breaker
title.description: The might of trolls crumbles in the face of such persistance as you have demonstrated.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Fierce
title.description: Warg howls pierce the dark, but they would do well to be silent lest they wish to follow their brethren to their doom by your hand.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Feather-duster
title.description: Your tireless efforts have harried the eyes of the foe, and the good peoples of Eregion need no longer to flinch from the spying gaze of the crebain.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bane of Dunland
title.description: The Dunlendings strive ever to rise and oppress the Free Peoples, for injuries of old have been stirred up in recent tumultuous events.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Just
title.description: The corrupted half-orcs have no place in the Elf-ruins of Eregion, and your stalwart efforts have done much to drive them away.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Vermin-bane
title.description: Many vile things roam the once-fair hills and plains of Eregion, but you have lessened their numbers.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Fang-breaker
title.description: Howls hover like smoke upon the winds of Eregion, darkening the passage of all who wander there, but you have brightened the land in your efforts against the Warg and wolf-voices.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Seeker of Deep Places
title.description: You have proven yourself before the Doors of Durin.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Rune-keeper's Foe
title.description: Sticks and stones win.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Slayer of Rune-keepers
title.description: All their scratching and drawings mean nothing with a weapon splitting their skulls.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Rune-smasher
title.description: What is best about the rune-keeper is the ease which they crumble before you.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Word-eater
title.description: Word will not hurt you, but the flesh of this enemy will fill your belly.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Lore-breaker
title.description: What is there that can be written that you cannot undo? Nothing. The lore of the past is gone and lost upon you.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Warden's Foe
title.description: Guardians of the forest? More like meat for the beasts!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Warden-slayer
title.description: Wardens prove no more sport for you than a slug.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Spear-breaker
title.description: Shattered spears lay about your feet when you meet this foe upon the field of battle.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Defender's Bane
title.description: Wardens fancy themselves defenders, ha! They are nothing before your mighty assault.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Legend-breaker
title.description: Legends amongst the heroes of the Free Peoples? No longer. These wardens are nothing more than pale stories of the vibrant Light.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Defender of Hollin
title.description: The Uruk captains were strong, but you proved yourself the stronger, and Eregion is now safer for all who wander there.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Protector of Hollin
title.description: You have spent many a day in Eregion and fought long to keep it safe.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Lore-seeker
title.description: Your thirst for knowledge has given you expertise in uncovering lost lore.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Saviour of the Forgotten Archive
title.description: Your defeat of the three chieftains of the Library of Tham Mírdain has proven you a hardy and valiant warrior.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Defender of the Crumbling School
title.description: Your defeat of the three chieftains of the School of Tham Mírdain has proven you a hardy and valiant warrior.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Forge-warden
title.description: Your defeat of the two guardians of the Ring-forge of Tham Mírdain has proven you a hardy and valiant warrior.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Protector of Mirobel
title.description: Your work to restore Tham Mírdain to its original state of preserved peace has given much hope to the Elves of Mirobel.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Diplomat
title.description: The greed of brigands brings only ruin to all that they touch, but you have done much to prevent their pillaging of Tham Mírdain.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Defier of Evil
title.description: Orcs are unabashedly cruel and merciless to their foes and even amongst their brethren, but you have defended the School of Tham Mírdain from their brutalisation.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Daring
title.description: The Uruks of the White Hand are a new threat to Tham Mírdain, but your efforts have slowed the destruction they would have wrought if left unchecked.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Patron of Mirobel
title.description: The Angmarim are unwelcome wherever they go, not the least in Tham Mírdain, but you have shown them that they are not wanted near Mirobel.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Sympathetic
title.description: The Pale-folk slaves have been adequately thanked for assisting the doings of their powerful masters.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Librarian
title.description: Your acquisition of the forgotten lore archives at Tham Mírdain has done much to enlighten your historical pursuits.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Tutor
title.description: Your acquisition of the aged instructional ledgers at Tham Mírdain has done much to enlighten your historical pursuits.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Student of Celebrimbor
title.description: Your acquisition of the lost manuals of Ring-lore at Tham Mírdain has done much to enlighten your historical pursuits.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Marshal of Tham Mírdain
title.description: The Elves of Rivendell hail you as a great Marshal for all that you have done to protect the peace of Tham Mírdain.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Ridge-racer
title.description: Your sure-footed steps upon the Hollin Ridge have given you some fame.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Curator of the Forgotten Treasury
title.description: Your tireless work to restore the Forgotten Treasury to its former glory has not gone unnoticed by the dwarves.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Treasure Hunter
title.description: Your sharp eyes have brought you fame for the lost riches you retrieved from the Forgotten Treasury.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Caretaker of the Forgotten Treasury
title.description: You have defeated many enemies of significance in the Forgotten Treasury.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Keeper of the Forgotten Treasury
title.description: The Forgotten Treasury has been purged of evil, thanks to your valiant efforts.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Custodian of the Forgotten Treasury
title.description: You have removed the threat presented by many enemies within the Forgotten Treasury.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Friend of the Nine
title.description: You have laid your own footsteps in those of the nine companions who set out from Rivendell.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Explorer of Khazad-dûm
title.description: Your tireless wanderings in Khazad-dûm have given you a keen awareness of which few dwarves could boast.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Worm-scourge
title.description: Worms of Moria are wholly evil, and your work against them has brought much hope to the dwarves.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Triumph within the Deeps
title.description: You have done valiant deeds for the free folk of Moria, and have brought light to that place where darkness reigns.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Smith of the Burning Deeps
title.description: Your experince with the implements of the Forges of Khazad-dûm has lent you renown as a smith.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Forge-breaker
title.description: You have defeated many enemies of significance in the Forges of Khazad-dûm.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Will-breaker
title.description: The goblins would be wise to flee next time you set foot in the Forges of Khazad-dûm, for their casualties were great.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Douser of Flames
title.description: Orcs of the Forges of Khazad-dûm will never forget the wrath you unleashed upon them as you passed through those halls.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Resilient
title.description: Trolls are deadly foes, but you have proven yourself far deadlier.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Infiltrator
title.description: You acquired many tools of the enemy in Fil Gashan, harrying their endeavours there.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Morale-smasher
title.description: You have defeated many enemies of significance in Fil Gashan.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Fighter
title.description: You have defeated so many fighters in Fil Gashan that you are reckoned a fighter also, but the title is kindly bestowed.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Skirmisher
title.description: You have defeated so many skirmishers in Fil Gashan that you are reckoned a skirmisher also, but the title is kindly bestowed.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bane of Industry
title.description: Your tireless work to restore the Forges of Khazad-dûm to their former glory has not gone unnoticed by the dwarves.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bane of Fil Gashan
title.description: Your tireless work to restore Fil Gashan to its former glory has not gone unnoticed by the dwarves.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Marshal of the Burning Depths
title.description: You are reckoned a great hero for your deeds in Fil Gashan and the Forges of Khazad-dûm.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Climber of Stairs
title.description: Your persistent exploration of the Grand Stair has led your feet upon many a step.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Braver of Heights
title.description: Your tireless work to restore the Grand Stair to its former glory has not gone unnoticed by the dwarves.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Interceptor
title.description: Your interception of texts and communications in the Grand Stair has been a bane to the plans of Igash.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Bold
title.description: You have defeated many enemies of significance in the Grand Stair.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Doom of Igash
title.description: The Grand Stair has been purged of evil, thanks to your valiant efforts.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Foe of the Warg-keepers
title.description: The Warg-Keepers of the Grand Stair will think twice before boasting their assured victory when they fall upon you in battle.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Valiant
title.description: Orcs in the Grand Stair quail at the memory of your vigilance against them.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Steady
title.description: Stupid and vicious trolls alike have been felled by your weapon, and the Grand Stair is less perilous thanks to you.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Foe of the Highpeak
title.description: There is fear in the fell voices of the Wargs that howl in the Grand Stair, for you bring certain doom to those accursed beasts.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, ${NAME: Watchman[m]| Watchwoman[f]}
title.description: Your tireless work to defend Moria from the wrath of the Watcher in the Water has not gone unnoticed by the dwarves.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Peace-bringer
title.description: Many dwarves were lost to the Watcher in the Water, but you have done well to discover their true fates.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Slayer of the Watcher
title.description: You have defeated the evil and malicious Watcher in the Water, and the dwarves of Moria hail you as a great warrior worthy of much renown.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Whip-lash
title.description: The arms of the Watcher in the Water are many, but you have hewn them.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Seeker of the Fallen
title.description: You have proven the fate of many brave souls who fell in Skûmfil.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, A Light in the Dark
title.description: Your tireless work to restore the Dark Delvings to their former glory has not gone unnoticed by the dwarves.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Diviner
title.description: You have discovered many Rune-stones in the Dark Delvings, earning your scholarly pursuits a great deal of respect.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Doom-breaker
title.description: You have defeated many enemies of significance in the Dark Delvings.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Brilliant
title.description: Glow-worms are deadly creatures, however fair their light, and you have done well to harry their reign of the Dark Delvings.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Slayer of the Nameless
title.description: The horrific and mysterious Nameless of the Dark Delvings no longer prowl as confidently as they did before your coming.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, ${NAME: Master[m]| Mistress[f]} Over Fear
title.description: Your tireless work to restore the Foundations of Stone to their former glory has not gone unnoticed by the dwarves.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Purifier of Skûmfil
title.description: Your tireless work to restore Skûmfil to its former glory has not gone unnoticed by the dwarves.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Grimreaver's Bane
title.description: You have defeated many enemies of significance in Skûmfil.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Brúmbereth's Bane
title.description: Skûmfil has been purged of evil, thanks to your valiant efforts.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Deep-cleaver
title.description: The numbers of threatening deep-claws in Skûmfil have been greatly thinned due to your watchful defence.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Shell-smasher
title.description: You have lessened the numbers of gredbyg in Skûmfil, making ventures there a little less unpleasant.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Nemesis of the Corpse-beasts
title.description: Foul Kergrim in Skûmfil will not be so deadly now that you have lessened their presence there.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Web-shredder
title.description: The spawn of Ungoliant have thrived in Skûmfil, but your mighty weapons and defences have curbed their malice.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Exterminator
title.description: Your tireless work to restore the Sixteenth Hall to its former glory has not gone unnoticed by the dwarves.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Blight-scourge
title.description: You have defeated many enemies of significance in the Sixteenth Hall.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Investigator
title.description: Your interest in the cause of the fungal disease has brought you deep into the Sixteenth Hall, and into many dangers.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Hearty
title.description: Orcs are horrible with or without an infectious disease, and the Sixteeth Hall is better off with the Orc presence lessened.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bug-stomper
title.description: Your defeat of many terrible insects in the Sixteenth Hall has earned you a fitting name.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Blight-cleanser
title.description: The elimination of infectious Orcs from the Sixteenth Hall is imperative, and you have done much to aid in this cause.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Champion of Eriador
title.description: Your valour and courage helped to throw down the Iron Crown of Angmar.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Motivating
title.description: Your selfless acts have raised the spirits of your companions, motivating them to greater deeds and victories!

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Deep-delver
title.description: Your fearless exploration of the enemy's keeps says much about your desire to triumph over your foes through knowledge of their whereabouts.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Master of the Anvil
title.description: You have earned renown for your efforts to defeat the foes of the Iron Garrison in the Halls of Crafting.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Crate-collector
title.description: You have proven a valuable resource for recovering much-needed supplies from the Halls of Crafting.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Redeemer of the Deep
title.description: Your defeat of the Mistress of Pestilence and her Nameless horde has made you a hero among the dwarves of the Iron Garrison.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Seeker of Toadstools
title.description: Your steadfast search for the cause of the terrible fungal plague raging through Moria has earned you great respect.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Gardener of the Deep
title.description: You collected several plant-samples from the works of Nalâ-dûm.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Engineer of Nalâ-dûm
title.description: Your efforts to drive the pests from Nalâ-dûm has aided in the return of the Water-works to active use.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Foe-bane
title.description: You have earned acclaim by the defeat of the Orc-leaders in the Halls of Crafting.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Rage of the Stonecarver
title.description: Your efforts to drive the Enemy from the Halls of Crafting is deemed ample tribute to the memory of Melkólf Stonecarver.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Arrow-breaker
title.description: You have proven quite skilled at managing the ranged aggressors in the Halls of Crafting.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Suppressor of Pestilence
title.description: You have proven yourself a match for the most vile creatures in the depths of Moria.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Cleanser of the Nameless
title.description: Nameless things dwell in the deep places of the world, but thanks to you, there are many fewer.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, the Eradicator
title.description: The Orcs of the Globsnaga fear your very approach.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Troll-tipper
title.description: Even the menacing trolls of the Globsnaga cower at the mention of your name.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Banisher of Darkness
title.description: More than just lizards dwell in the works of Nalâ-dûm. You encountered and defeated a mighty Caerog, as well.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Cold-blooded
title.description: Over the centuries, Nalâ-dûm has become a spawning ground for pesky lizards. You have greatly reduced their number.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Defender of Caras Galadhon
title.description: You are revered for your heroic acts in defence of Caras Galadhon.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Poacher of the Protected Woods
title.description: You are both revered and reviled for your hunting skills.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Cake-eater
title.description: You really love lembas bread.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Blind Leaper
title.description: You are sure you have fallen in every pit from the Hollin Gate to the East Gate of Moria.

title.description: You found the bottom of a well...the hard way.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Lórien Lookout
title.description: You are honoured for helping stand guard upon the flets of Lothlórien.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Wild Hunter
title.description: You have become a respected hunter among the Galadhrim.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Champion of Lothlórien
title.description: The Orcs of Moria will not soon assault Lórien, thanks to you.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Defender of Lórien
title.description: The Elves of Lórien have rejoiced at your victories against the Orcs of Moria.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Trueheart Defender of Lórien
title.description: You have fought bravely with the Elves of Lórien against the Orcs of Moria many, many times.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, of Victory in Lórien
title.description: You are one of the few who has won a truly legendary victory during the Battle of Lórien.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Fleeting Ally of Lórien
title.description: You fought with the Elves of Lórien against the Orcs of Moria.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Steadfast Ally of Lórien
title.description: You have won several victories in Lórien against the Orcs of Moria.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Persistent Defender of Lórien
title.description: Your victories against the Orcs of Moria have brought you great renown among the Elves of Lórien.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Guest of Lothlórien
title.description: The Galadhrim of Lothlórien welcome you as an enemy of the Orcs in Moria.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Guardian of Lothlórien
title.description: Your actions on behalf of the Galadhrim have earned you great favour.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Warrior of Lothlórien
title.description: The Galadhrim sing the praises of your prowess and courage in the face of hopeless danger.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Bringer of Light
title.description: You were able to collect enough mirror-shards from Lumul-nar to give the Iron Garrison hope that the mirror-works may be restored.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Defender of the Hidden Dawn
title.description: Your efforts to free Lumul-nar from the clutches of the merrevail have restored the hope that the light of the dawn may once again shine in the halls of Khazad-dûm.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Slayer of the Shadows
title.description: The merrevail and their Warg allies sought to keep the light from Lumul-nar, but your defeat of their leaders became their undoing.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME} the Silencer
title.description: The merrevail of Lumul-nar were no match for your determination. Their screams no longer echo in the halls.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Avenger of Khazad-dûm
title.description: You have aided the dwarves of the Iron Garrison to establish a foothold against the Orcs of Mazog.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Stalwart against the Shadow
title.description: You have defeated Mazog and aided the Iron Garrison and the Galadhrim against even greater threats.

title.name: ${RANK}${RANK: [E]}${NAME}${SURNAME: [E]}${SURNAME}, Doer of Great Deeds
